fields.name: Andes Nevado 300 sleeping bag
fields.description: The Andes Nevado 300 sleeping bag has been certified to EN ISO 23537-1:2016 standards and awarded temperature ratings: Comfort 7°C/45ºF, Limit 2°C/36ºF and Extreme -13°C/9ºF.  The mummy shaped sleeping bag is the most thermally efficient. Wide at the shoulders with a pronounced taper to a narrow foot, reducing the amount of space and air to be heated within the bag.

fields.name: Stormbreak 2
fields.description: This classic two-person tent has a large domed design with two doors and two twin-zip, multi-configuration vestibules for easy access in and out. Not only that, but you can easily stuff them into the adjacent mesh pockets to keep them out of the way. The shape allows for an abundance of headroom and high-low ventilation for maximum breathability, while the fully seam-sealed canopy and floor keep you warm, dry and ready for a day of adventure.

fields.name: 6 Person Vis A Vis Tent
fields.description: This 6 Person Vis A Vis Tent is the home away from home, with 2 large separate bedrooms and a spacious central living area you will have plenty of room to enjoy your holiday. It has colour coded poles which make pitching a breeze. It's double skin will prevent condensation and cable access point so you can keep all of your gadgets charged.

fields.name: Camping tent mh100 - 2-person
fields.description: This tent has a classic dome structure. All you have to do is fit the tent poles with the bedroom, and then fit the flysheet on top.If it is windy it is advisable to attach the guy ropes that are provided in the tent bag.

The “Urban Garden” trend has made growing fresh greenery at home possible and very popular: balcony, rooftop, windowsill, patio; any indoor garden can give the pleasure of gardening if you choose the right grow kit.

fields.name: Herb Seeds Set: Herbs Seeds for Planting

fields.name: Ireland's Hidden Medicine: An exploration of Irish indigenous medicine from legend and myth to the present day
fields.description: Rosarie Kingston’s new book explores the rich healing traditions of Ireland which resonate through the country’s landscape, music, festivals and language. Indigenous medicine, no matter where it exists in the world, is characterised by the oral transmission of knowledge and the necessity for each person to be in harmony with themselves, their society and environment, as well as the spirit world. Ireland is no different, and its traditional therapeutic approach is designed to address body, mind, spirit and emotions within the local social and environmental context.

fields.name: The Handmade Apothecary: Healing herbal remedies: Healing herbal recipes
fields.description: Herbs are quite literally everywhere; it is only our ability to recognise their value that has been lost. Vicky and Kim explore the traditional uses of herbs combined with a modern and scientific understanding of a truly holistic approach so that you can use herbs to treat ailments and improve your general wellbeing.
